description: In a time when gods and demons walked the earth as men, a young warrior raises his sword to the skies and declares defiance! Dagar the Invincible is a hero of blade and sandal, and Dark Horse Books uncovers the exciting legend of his journey through the ancient, mystical world! The first of two volumes in this archival series introduces Dagar and tales of his quest, originally published by Gold Key Comics in the 1970s. Collects Dagar the Invincible #1-#9.

description: Tyreke White has had a horrible day…and now he’s about to have an even worse night. Forgetting his cell phone on his desk after a late day at work, Tyreke is now stranded because his car broke down in a bad neighborhood of Newport City. A neighborhood that is so unsavory that when he was a child, Tyreke’s mother had made up a nursery rhyme to scare him from ever going into areas like this one in order to keep him safe. Despite being grown up now, that precautionary, imaginary childhood tale is about to become a harsh, brutal reality...
name: Not Tonight In Newport

description: The deviant minds of Joe Casey (Wildcats, Superman) and Charlie Adlard (X-Files,Astronauts in Trouble) present this gritty tale of violence and morality. By day, Cameron Daltrey is an L.A. bail bondsman for superhuman freaks. By night, he's a masked bounty hunter taking out his aggressions on those same bail-skipping freaks.
name: TPB

description:
BACK AT IMAGE IN AN ALL-NEW FULL COLOR COLLECTION!

A cult hit is back, the way it was always meant to be seen, from co-creators JOE CASEY (GODLAND) and CHARLIE ADLARD (THE WALKING DEAD). Cameron Daltrey is an L.A. bail bondsman. His specialty is criminals of the superhuman persuasion, the type who rarely make their court dates. And so Cameron leads an interesting double life: bail bondsman by day, masked bounty hunter by night. Packed with extra features, INCLUDING AN ALL-NEW CODEFLESH STORY BY CASEY & ADLARD - THE FIRST IN SEVEN YEARS!
name: HC

description:
Odin is seated on the throne of Asgard once more. Now learn ye now the story of the World Tree – the birth of spacetime itself! Speaking of Odin... guess who's got one eye and isn't exactly thrilled to see young Loki again? And as the refugees of nine worlds brace for the relentless invasion by the dark gods of the Tenth World, hoping against hope they'll live to see tomorrow, two of Asgard's most mighty ready themselves to make the ultimate sacrifice! This is it, true believers – the last moment of daylight before the skies rip open and rain down blood... and the World Eaters... next stop Midgard!

Plus, Baron Zemo takes his battle against the new Captain America to a new and terrifying level!

Also, Tony Stark and Sasha Hammer, finally meet face to face. The gang at Stark Resilient burn the midnight oil against an impossible deadline – but if they don't get Project Daylight off the ground they're doomed before they start. They're not the only one manufacturing their world-changer, though – the Hammer Girls are building an army of drone bombers as air support for Detroit Steel!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #608, Thor Vol.1 #619 and Invincible Iron Man Vol.5 #30!

description:
As the super-powered descendants of coupled aliens and humans, the WildC.A.T.S covertly protected the Earth from the extraterrestrial invasion of the Daemonites and their plans of world domination. But after finally ending the alien threat, the disillusioned and splintered team of super-heroes unceremoniously disbanded on bad terms. Now, amid feelings of distrust and animosity, the mercenary Grifter, the size-manipulating Maul, the shape-shifting Voodoo, and the android Spartan are forced to reunite in order to take down a megalomaniac who is using the Daemonites' technology for his own plans of planetary conquest.

Collects Wildcats, (Vol. 2, 1999), #1-6.
name: Vol. 1

description: As a group of super-powered human and alien hybrids, the WildC.A.T.S have risked their lives countless times to protect the world against threats of invasion and conquest. But when the team heads to Las Vegas to battle an immortal villain, they realize their greatest fear as one of their own dies. A tragic book of secret revelations and new beginnings, this intense volume features the exploits of Spartan, the indestructible alien android, Grifter, the psionic-powered mercenary, Void, the dimension-shifting energy being, Maul, the size-manipulating scientist, Ladytron, the reformed killer cyborg, and Voodoo, the shape-shifting telepath.
name: Vol. 2

description: The controversial storyline that changed the WildCats forever is collected in SERIAL BOXES, reprinting WILDCATS Volume 2 issues #14-19. A young serial killer named Slaughterhouse Smith sets out on a vendetta against Jacob Marlowe...and anyone who shares his name! The entire WILDCATS cast is drawn into this modern horror story — a relentless tale of violence and retribution — where no one gets out unscathed.
name: Vol. 3

description: The team members of the WildCats underwent a series of life-shattering events in WILDCATS: SERIAL BOXES. Will they be able to pick up the pieces and carry on? This volume — collecting WILDCATS (Volume 2) #20-28 by writer Joe Casey (ADVENTURES OF SUPERMAN, AUTOMATIC KAFKA, Uncanny X-Men) and artists Sean Phillips (SLEEPER) and Steve Dillon (PREACHER) — answers that very question, as the team faces the traumatic aftermath of SERIAL BOXES. In this story, Grifter finally discovers the true fate of Zealot. Maul's research brings unwanted attention from the government. Spartan faces down a hostile takeover of the Halo Corporation. And the grievously injured Voodoo discovers an unexpected benefit of her hybrid genetics.
name: Vol. 4
